# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // ~√(0.5)

// Physics/simulation configuration
var config = {
    attraction: 4000,          // Repulsion force strength
    springCoeff: 0.004,        // Spring coefficient for edges
    amplification: 0.92,       // Velocity damping factor
    gravityPull: 0.0003,       // Gravity toward center
    maxParticles: 40,          // Max number of stream particles
    streamDecay: 0.04,         // Particle decay rate
    theta: 0.06               // Camera smoothing factor
};

// === NODES (graph vertices) ===
var nodes = [
    { id: 'hub',      label: 'Hub',      r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'alpha',    label: 'Alpha',    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'beta',     label: 'Beta',     r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'gamma',    label: 'Gamma',    r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'delta',    label: 'Delta',    r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'epsilon',  label: 'Epsilon',  r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// === EDGES (spring connections between nodes) ===
var edges = [
    { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle stream
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Main physics step: repulsion + springs + gravity + damping
function physicsStep() {
    // 1) Node-node repulsion (inverse-square law)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Spring forces along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.springCoeff) * displacement;
        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) Gravity toward center (400, 300) + velocity damping + position update
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.gravityPull;
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.gravityPull;
        nodes[n].vx *= config.amplification;  // damping
        nodes[n].vy *= config.amplification;
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a decorative particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.maxParticles) return;
    var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;
    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update particles: move, decay, remove dead ones
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
            continue;
        }
        p.vx *= 1 - (config.streamDecay * 0.125);
        p.vy *= 1 - (config.streamDecay * 0.125);
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
    }
}

// Smooth camera interpolation toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.theta;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.theta;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}

// Main loop tick
function tick() {
    physicsStep();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    frameCount++;
}

// Run at ~60fps (16ms interval)
setInterval(tick, 16);
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation engine** — the physics backend for a network visualization. Here's the summary:

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **6 Nodes** | "Hub" (central), Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon — positioned in a ~800×600 space |
| **8 Spring Edges** | Connect nodes with Hooke's law springs (rest lengths 160–220px) |
| **Repulsion** | All nodes repel each other via inverse-square force (like electric charges) |
| **Gravity** | Gentle pull toward center point (400, 300) to prevent drift |
| **Damping** | Velocities multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent oscillation |
| **Particles** | Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward, and fade/die |
| **Camera** | Smooth-interpolating camera with position and zoom (lerp factor 0.06) |

**In short:** It's the **simulation-only layer** (no rendering code) of an interactive node-graph visualization — like a small constellation or network map with ambient floating particles. The nodes settle into a stable equilibrium where spring attraction and charge repulsion balance out. A renderer (not included) would read the node/particle positions to draw the scene.
